cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with gesture recognition in video, which is a task related to computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new neural network architecture, which involves deep learning techniques such as recurrence and convolutions, making it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on a gesture recognition dataset, which falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
